Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.12,0:00:05.81,DCMain,NARRATION,0000,0000,0000,,Progressing steadily towards \Nthe next phase of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.08,0:00:10.38,DCMain,NARRATION,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to your support, we \Nmake progress every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.45,0:00:18.01,DCMain,NARRATION,0000,0000,0000,,Running from Nagoya to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.50,0:00:24.46,DCMain,NARRATION,0000,0000,0000,,The Toto Railway is a proud sponsor \Nof the World Sports Games.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.46,0:00:25.80,DCItalic,,0000,0000,0000,,The Toto Railway is a proud sponsor \Nof the World Sports Games.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:31.43,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, if you find any \Nlarge pieces of garbage,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.46,0:00:30.92,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs28\bord2\shad0\c&H00C4F1&\3c&HFFFFFF&\b1}Flower Road {\c&H9761FA&}Experience
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.43,0:00:33.84,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,don't touch it and let me know instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.05,0:00:37.50,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.50,0:00:41.22,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we have to clean \Nup the shopping center?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.05,0:00:45.00,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,This is part of our class, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:48.69,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's an activity for getting \Nto know our local community.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.02,0:00:53.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It may be part of class,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.53,0:00:56.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but that doesn't mean picking up \Ntrash isn't a pain in the butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.56,0:01:02.05,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,If we pick up their garbage, it'll \Nmake it harder for adults to litter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.05,0:01:03.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.24,0:01:08.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much we pick up, \Npeople will never stop littering.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.26,0:01:11.45,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about the garbage right here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.45,0:01:17.25,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ayumi-chan, stop playing with that \Nstray cat and help us over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.25,0:01:18.97,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a stray.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.09,0:01:23.22,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.92,0:01:26.42,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.42,0:01:28.48,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here? Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.14,0:01:32.47,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,That's Isojima-san's cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.76,0:01:35.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isojima-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.29,0:01:35.99,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.37,0:01:39.92,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}She always cleans up around this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.57,0:01:39.99,Isojima,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,433)}Isojima Chiemi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.87,0:01:44.37,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,But recently Isojima-san \Nhasn't been feeling well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.37,0:01:46.50,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,She's in the hospital right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.11,0:01:53.34,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that cat thought they'd get to \Nsee their owner if they came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.18,0:01:58.30,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what the heck is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.30,0:02:02.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought adults weren't supposed to \Nlitter while kids are cleaning up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.84,0:02:04.66,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,This is pretty awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.02,0:02:07.52,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs30\b1\bord2\shad0\c&H8D6845&\3c&HDFC994&\blur3}Notice\N\N{\fs26}Please do not dispose of household \Ngarbage or dog poop in this bin\N\NBeika City Shopping Center
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.87,0:02:08.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like there used\Nto be a garbage bin here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.26,0:02:11.21,DCMain,KOBAYASHI,0000,0000,0000,,There definitely was, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.21,0:02:14.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then where did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.19,0:02:18.03,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.93,0:02:20.66,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I feel someone watching me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.29,0:02:23.16,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.77,0:02:29.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A journey of a thousand miles \Nstarts with the first step!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.34,0:02:31.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Solve 1,000 mysteries and enter a new world!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.45,0:02:33.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The shopping center is excited for the WSG!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.48,0:02:35.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Trouble with trash reveals \Na surprising blind spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:37.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:38.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.95,0:02:41.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.99,0:04:28.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,1)}The Beika City Shopping \NCenter Garbage Bin Mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.37,0:04:26.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Beika City Shopping \NCenter Garbage Bin Mystery!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.34,0:04:31.65,DCMain,TEACHER,0000,0000,0000,,The World Sports Games.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.65,0:04:37.25,DCMain,TEACHER,0000,0000,0000,,It's an international sports festival \Nheld once every four years,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.25,0:04:39.60,DCMain,TEACHER,0000,0000,0000,,and this year, it's being held in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.32,0:04:44.51,DCMain,TEACHER,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Tokyo is hosting the WSG.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.79,0:04:48.74,DCMain,TEACHER,0000,0000,0000,,So we're asking students of all \Nyears and classes to submit ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.74,0:04:51.27,DCMain,TEACHER,0000,0000,0000,,for entertaining the guests coming to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.61,0:04:57.03,DCMain,TEACHER,0000,0000,0000,,The best ideas will be implemented \Nhere at Teitan High School!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.28,0:05:03.40,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, they were originally a stray cat,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:05.90,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,so they get outside sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.90,0:05:10.41,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,But it's okay. They always come \Nhome when it's time to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.55,0:05:14.67,DCItalic,YAIBA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yaiba Punch! Yaiba Kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.40,0:05:15.04,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's Kamen Yaiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:18.70,DCItalic,YAIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Purchase Kamen Yaiba Chocolate \Nand shake hands with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.70,0:05:23.47,DCItalic,NARRATION,0000,0000,0000,,Kamen Yaiba Chocolate manufacturer Mitsuzuka \Nis a proud sponsor of WSG Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.33,0:05:31.12,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking forward to \Nwatching WSG Tokyo with my cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.52,0:05:37.02,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,But in my current condition, I can \Nbarely get around in a wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.02,0:05:39.54,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go home yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.34,0:05:47.16,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But you were well enough to clean \Nthe shopping center until recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.16,0:05:49.02,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.02,0:05:50.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.62,0:05:53.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why the garbage \Nbin that was here is gone now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.13,0:05:56.29,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that garbage bin?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.86,0:06:03.47,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever I cleaned this area,\NI'd dispose of my garbage in this bin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.98,0:06:10.31,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,The bin is probably gone because there's a \Nfeud going on at the nearby store association.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.90,0:06:13.76,DCMain,BAKER,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.10,0:06:19.51,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.85,0:06:22.02,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.92,0:06:24.53,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,...you didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.40,0:06:27.75,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,...drop something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.11,0:06:30.65,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,We're sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.65,0:06:32.06,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.06,0:06:34.50,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,They ran off without picking up their trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.18,0:06:42.67,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,This is all the fault of you eateries!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.97,0:06:44.18,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.18,0:06:46.55,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the shopping center \Nis overflowing with trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.71,0:06:49.93,Isojima,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,438)\pos(470,317)}Deli
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.71,0:06:49.93,Isojima,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,438)\pos(150,317)}Japanese-style Cafe
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.73,0:06:50.01,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're wrong. It's because \Nthere are more tourists.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:52.30,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,It's a problem for us, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.47,0:06:55.68,Isojima,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,432)\pos(451,317)\3c&H7A3844&}Bicycle Shop
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.47,0:06:55.68,Isojima,SIGN MIDDLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,432)\pos(196,319)\3c&H8C515B&}Clothing Shop
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.47,0:06:55.68,Isojima,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,432)\pos(65,317)\3c&H8C515B&}Bookstore
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.58,0:06:56.24,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That's because you eateries recommend that \Npeople walk and eat at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.24,0:06:58.31,DCMain,CLOTHING,0000,0000,0000,,That's why there's garbage all over town.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:06:59.94,Isojima,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,1)\pos(327,317)\3c&H92596D&}Florist
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.47,0:06:59.94,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.08,0:07:04.57,DCMain,CLOTHING,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, it sounds like the \Neateries should install garbage bins.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.78,0:07:09.70,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,Why should we be the only \Nones to pay for garbage bins?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.70,0:07:12.49,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the store \Nassociation budget is for.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.69,0:07:17.01,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Most of the litter around town comes \Nfrom people walking and eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.42,0:07:16.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, you're part of the store association?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.85,0:07:18.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here representing Poirot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.01,0:07:18.93,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.93,0:07:25.06,DCMain,CLOTHING,0000,0000,0000,,We're currently experiencing \Nproblems because of you eateries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.62,0:07:29.76,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,But that's no reason for you to remove \Nthe garbage bin in the empty lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:32.51,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,Now there's trash all over the empty lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.70,0:07:36.51,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,That garbage bin was paid for using \Nthe store association budget.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.84,0:07:40.77,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,But recently, most of the litter around \Ntown comes from people walking and eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.90,0:07:44.24,DCMain,BOOKSTORE,0000,0000,0000,,And it was constantly overflowing. \NIt wasn't very sanitary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.24,0:07:48.65,DCMain,CLOTHING,0000,0000,0000,,You eateries should've been \Nfrequently collecting the trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.84,0:07:52.28,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we the only ones \Nresponsible for collecting it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:53.95,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:56.36,DCMain,CLOTHING,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Because most of it comes from \Npeople walking and eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.56,0:07:56.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.36,0:07:57.91,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,That's because there aren't \Nenough garbage bins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.28,0:08:08.60,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there? Who's watching me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.50,0:08:17.71,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.42,0:08:23.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I feel like the number \Nof garbage bins around town has decreased.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:27.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently it's because people throw \Ntheir trash into garbage bins,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.38,0:08:29.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,even if they're overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.56,0:08:34.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And installing bins and \Ncollecting trash costs money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.66,0:08:39.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, the store association \Nwas arguing about that today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.98,0:08:47.67,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? We're playing games at \Nthe professor's house again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.85,0:08:50.34,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Same old, same old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.34,0:08:51.67,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.71,0:08:58.72,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:03.00,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with people? We worked \Nso hard to clean this up yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.00,0:09:04.95,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously. It's unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.95,0:09:06.49,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,All right, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.49,0:09:07.44,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.59,0:09:08.19,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:10.65,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.32,0:09:12.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:16.45,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys will find the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.45,0:09:18.49,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.49,0:09:19.51,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.09,0:09:23.62,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Who dumped their trash?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.88,0:09:27.43,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, where the garbage bin \Nused to be in the empty lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.43,0:09:29.97,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,Probably someone walking and eating again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.97,0:09:32.88,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But there was other trash, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.13,0:09:36.20,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,Well... no, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.20,0:09:39.68,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the guys who run the eateries did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.82,0:09:44.43,DCMain,MITSHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why would the store \Nowners dump garbage there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.43,0:09:47.21,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,So we'll put back the garbage bin we removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.21,0:09:49.59,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,You said there was trash besides \Nfood-related garbage, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.14,0:09:53.44,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.82,0:09:58.64,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,Why would someone dump all \Ntheir trash in a place
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.16,0:10:00.95,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,where there used to be a garbage bin?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.34,0:10:04.70,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,That was probably the \Nwork of the bicycle shop
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.70,0:10:07.58,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,and the other stores opposed \Nto installing garbage bins.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.11,0:10:09.46,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.90,0:10:12.33,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:16.47,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the other stores \Ndump garbage there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.95,0:10:21.47,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,To force the eateries to \Ninstall a garbage bin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.67,0:10:25.29,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,They claim most of the litter comes \Nfrom people walking and eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.82,0:10:28.94,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,A little more to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:29.60,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.60,0:10:31.45,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,That's your left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.45,0:10:31.94,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,This way?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.20,0:10:34.57,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, attach it around there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.57,0:10:35.28,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.28,0:10:36.19,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.54,0:10:39.30,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. How does it look, Ai-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.30,0:10:42.23,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Looks good. Now walk sideways.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:44.70,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Can you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:47.20,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I can see you clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.53,0:10:49.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.28,0:10:54.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Now we should get \Na great look at the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.53,0:11:18.75,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.31,0:11:29.04,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,How about maps of phone charging locations
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.04,0:11:33.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and WiFi hotspots for foreigners \Nthat are written in English?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.85,0:11:36.00,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That seems cliché, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.15,0:11:38.40,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then... I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.40,0:11:41.92,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,How about a map showing the foreign \Ncuisine restaurants in Beika City
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.92,0:11:46.01,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,for when the foreigners are feeling homesick?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.86,0:11:51.13,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any restaurants \Nlike that around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.13,0:11:55.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? You come up with some ideas, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.72,0:11:56.81,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.81,0:12:00.03,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I'm right on \Nthe verge of an epiphany.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.18,0:12:04.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.59,0:12:05.66,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.66,0:12:08.79,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a little late for you \Nto be walking home from school?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:11.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I took a little detour.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.01,0:12:17.24,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You were playing games at the \Nprofessor's house again, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.24,0:12:18.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.49,0:12:19.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Soccer, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.37,0:12:20.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:24.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.24,0:12:31.45,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Are you all on your \Nway home from school?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:34.87,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Are you coming back from \Nyour college classes as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.87,0:12:37.94,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You dummy, Subaru-san is a grad student.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:41.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're a grad student at the Toto \NUniversity Engineering School, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.01,0:12:44.57,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you remember, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.78,0:12:49.20,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This tote bag sure is cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.72,0:12:52.42,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you keep in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.42,0:12:53.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.53,0:12:56.57,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.57,0:13:00.37,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,It's a circuit board for \Nmeasuring electronic noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.37,0:13:02.84,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I use it in my grad school classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.18,0:13:05.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it's the receiver \Nfor a listening device.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.15,0:13:07.61,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.61,0:13:11.22,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,It's called a tester.\NIt's for measuring voltage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.55,0:13:13.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably a bug detector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:18.13,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Subaru-san. Jeez, Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.61,0:13:22.89,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but doesn't this bag look \Nso cool that you wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.89,0:13:24.97,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,expect to find \Nsuch lame stuff inside of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.97,0:13:26.03,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.90,0:13:29.31,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The inside is divided.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.31,0:13:30.28,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.72,0:13:35.80,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Since I use it to transport precision \Ninstruments, it has cushioned partitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.80,0:13:37.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.11,0:13:42.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you're walking around with that stuff, does\Nthat mean you're doing something for the FBI?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.02,0:13:46.63,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.11,0:13:50.39,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The man who outwardly presents \Nhimself as grad student Okiya Subaru
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.88,0:13:55.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,is actually FBI agent Akai Shuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:00.40,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But that's a story for another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.28,0:14:05.44,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.96,0:14:07.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What the?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.98,0:14:14.41,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? We're playing games at \Nthe professor's house again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.60,0:14:17.30,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Same old, same old.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.30,0:14:18.85,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.85,0:14:22.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are always having \Nthe same conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.37,0:14:25.38,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:28.80,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with people? We \Njust cleaned this up yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.29,0:14:30.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.30,0:14:39.39,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's showing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.63,0:14:41.65,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Someone came.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.88,0:14:45.59,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He's acting suspiciously.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.44,0:14:48.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, isn't he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.98,0:14:50.36,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.36,0:14:51.53,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\fs30\bord3\shad0\c&H413AC1&\3c&H4EE5F9&}Handmade Side Dishes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.74,0:14:53.87,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I buy croquettes at his store all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.57,0:14:55.28,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.62,0:15:00.51,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,That's one tuna corn dog and one \Ncod roe croquette rice ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.46,0:15:02.99,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.99,0:15:07.26,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I just went to check it \Nout because I noticed the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.66,0:15:10.38,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed you noticed from so far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.38,0:15:13.27,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,Despite how I look, I've got a keen eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.27,0:15:16.48,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But mister, it looked like you were \Ncarefully observing your surroundings
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.48,0:15:19.13,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,as you approached the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.67,0:15:24.69,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,That's because I was wondering \Nwhat the camera was filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:26.49,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.49,0:15:28.52,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.52,0:15:30.63,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, you're interfering with my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.63,0:15:31.94,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.94,0:15:33.20,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.07,0:15:37.72,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,That guy is definitely suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.72,0:15:41.33,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He's the only one caught on camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.62,0:15:42.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.15,0:15:44.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.69,0:15:48.05,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What is that? I'll rewind \Nthe video a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.88,0:15:50.67,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Something came down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.81,0:15:52.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could you play that again in slow motion?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.62,0:15:53.43,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.82,0:15:56.81,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's a crow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.12,0:15:58.73,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Just a crow?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.73,0:16:01.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's possible that \Nthe crow is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.38,0:16:02.36,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:08.12,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard that crows \Nwill gather food or trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.12,0:16:10.49,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then is this crow the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.49,0:16:15.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara, can you tell if this \Ncrow has any trash in its beak?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.59,0:16:17.53,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Give me one minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.81,0:16:20.36,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Apply high-speed digital signal processing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.33,0:16:25.99,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,reduce noise, and adjust contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.66,0:16:28.86,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably the best I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.83,0:16:33.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like this crow \Nhas anything in its beak.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.64,0:16:36.45,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Our theory about the crow being \Nthe culprit has fallen apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:38.89,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then was it that man after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:41.64,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,If only the camera had \Ncaught him dumping trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.80,0:16:46.40,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,We did set up the camera at an angle \Nthat would capture the person's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.25,0:16:51.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this camera has a blind spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.00,0:16:52.41,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,That is what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.41,0:16:55.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then couldn't we determine \Nthe range of that blind spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.20,0:16:59.06,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Based on our calculations,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.06,0:17:01.49,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,we've determined that the \Ncamera captures an adult
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.49,0:17:04.64,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,from the knees up no matter \Nwhere they approach from.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.53,0:17:08.46,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,However, once they're right \Nin front of the camera,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.81,0:17:10.97,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,we can't see what's below it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.97,0:17:13.54,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,That height is roughly 115 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.54,0:17:17.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, a culprit shorter than 115 \Ncentimeters wouldn't be caught on camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.44,0:17:20.60,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,But even if there were a culprit like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.91,0:17:22.97,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,in order to avoid being caught on camera,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.97,0:17:26.38,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,they'd have to approach from the fence side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:27.10,Not Visible,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(689,1)}Not Visible
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:27.10,Not Visible,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(234,75)\fad(689,1)}Not Visible
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.64,0:17:27.10,Not Visible,SIGN MIDDLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(356,214)\3c&H485D5F&\c&HF9FFFF&\fad(1071,1)}Visible
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.26,0:17:30.34,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anybody that small?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.34,0:17:34.06,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean a tiny child is the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.06,0:17:34.91,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.33,0:17:38.87,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I look closely, there's a hole here,\Nlike something passed through the bushes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.28,0:17:40.15,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.15,0:17:40.52,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.52,0:17:41.87,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What made this hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.62,0:17:45.87,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, did you figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.30,0:17:47.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.86,0:17:49.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.87,0:17:54.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isojima-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.49,0:17:57.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There something we'd like to ask you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.72,0:18:03.14,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9\fs30\bord2\shad0\fnArial\c&HC0E5F0&\3c&H1D98A5&}Beika City Store Association\N{\c&H59B8E5&\3c&H0F869B&}Office
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.86,0:18:03.14,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.48,0:18:05.91,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,You figured out who's been dumping trash?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.91,0:18:06.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:09.77,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,You mean they were captured on that camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.98,0:18:11.92,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.92,0:18:14.40,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,First, take a look at this image.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.25,0:18:18.45,DCMain,CLOTHING,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't the camera seem a bit low?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.45,0:18:21.28,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be able to see the culprit's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.70,0:18:23.54,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, isn't that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.92,0:18:26.04,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,...Isojima-san's cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.04,0:18:29.34,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,So the creature who was gathering \Ngarbage in that place every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.34,0:18:31.04,DCMain,BOOKSTORE,0000,0000,0000,,...was the cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.31,0:18:35.35,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Isojima-san would clean that area every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.35,0:18:40.73,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,She said she'd dispose of the trash she \Ncollected in the garbage bin at that empty lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.73,0:18:43.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We asked Isojima-san about it yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.81,0:18:45.17,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.17,0:18:46.56,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,You might be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.92,0:18:51.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why this cat has continued \Nto collect trash in this place
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.51,0:18:53.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,where the bin used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.38,0:18:54.93,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.93,0:18:58.95,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you snuck out \Nof the house every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.96,0:19:05.45,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, I'm terribly sorry for \Nthe trouble my cat has caused.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.61,0:19:07.40,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.40,0:19:08.58,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.11,0:19:14.21,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get better soon so I can get \Nback to cleaning with this cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.42,0:19:16.26,DCMain,DELI,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.26,0:19:19.45,DCMain,CAFE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should reinstall the garbage bin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.45,0:19:22.72,DCMain,CANDY,0000,0000,0000,,We should install some in areas where \Npeople are likely to walk and eat, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.04,0:19:25.85,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll be reinstalling \Nthe garbage bin at the lot
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:28.73,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,as well as several more in other locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.11,0:19:32.80,DCMain,BICYCLE,0000,0000,0000,,But the store association budget \Nisn't enough to cover that, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.80,0:19:34.65,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:36.15,DCMain,BOOKSTORE,0000,0000,0000,,Then what are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.15,0:19:37.73,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:41.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you use this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.39,0:19:42.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.16,0:19:47.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Our class' idea is being \Nturned into a product.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.43,0:19:50.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It was mostly Ran-kun's idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.27,0:19:51.65,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.77,0:19:54.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A tote bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.37,0:19:56.54,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not just any ordinary tote bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.09,0:19:59.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I call it the "garbage takeout bag."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.50,0:20:03.80,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(279,682)\fs30\bord2\shad0\fnArial\pos(319,253)\fscx213\fscy167\blur2\3c&H5F5849&}Garbage Takeout Bag
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.23,0:20:03.58,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}At first glance, it looks like an ordinary \Ntote bag with a Japanese-style pattern,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.58,0:20:07.14,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,but when you hang a garbage bag \Noff of the clips inside the bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:11.39,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,it turns into a partition that allows \Nyou to separate out your trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.84,0:20:16.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You can put dirty things \Ninside the trash bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.36,0:20:17.60,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.60,0:20:21.30,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,it's a bag that lets you take home \Nwhatever garbage you produce.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.30,0:20:23.62,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But because of its attractive appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.62,0:20:26.07,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,it doesn't look like you're \Ncarrying trash around with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.66,0:20:28.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,So if you use it without \Nattaching a garbage bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.88,0:20:31.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,it functions as a reusable shopping bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.84,0:20:34.77,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And since it folds up so small,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.77,0:20:37.75,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,it makes a great souvenir for foreigners.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.75,0:20:40.21,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I hope they take home both the idea \Nof bringing their trash home with them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.21,0:20:43.84,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and a piece of Japanese \Nculture as a souvenir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.05,0:20:45.66,DCMain,CLOTHING,0000,0000,0000,,How nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.66,0:20:47.97,DCMain,CLOTHING,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to sell those at my store.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.29,0:20:51.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We'd love to have you sell \Nthem in the shopping center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.85,0:20:56.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you use the profits \Nto install more garbage bins?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.27,0:20:57.86,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,What a wonderful idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.12,0:21:02.83,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use those bags and garbage \Nbins to clean up the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.83,0:21:04.24,DCMain,ISOJIMA,0000,0000,0000,,How marvelous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.72,0:21:09.97,DCMain,FLORIST,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone okay with \Nproceeding with this plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.97,0:21:11.24,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.80,0:21:15.49,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Your Ran-neechan did a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.32,0:22:46.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.16,0:22:47.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An invitation to a party?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.97,0:22:48.94,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.94,0:22:53.97,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Only WSG Tokyo sponsors can attend the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.40,0:22:58.23,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently several of Sonoko's \Ndad's companies are sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.99,0:23:01.10,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,So why are you inviting us?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.42,0:23:05.45,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko said it was a reward for finding \Nthe culprit who was dumping the trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.45,0:23:07.99,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You kids had better be on your best behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.21,0:23:11.94,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really get it, but it sounds \Nlike we'll be treated to great food.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.74,0:23:14.87,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I know this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.12,0:23:19.58,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's the newly constructed big \Nhotel by the Toto Railway Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.77,0:23:21.01,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.01,0:23:23.50,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I bet they have tons of tasty food.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.71,0:23:28.51,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Like eel, and eel, and eel...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.68,0:23:32.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And that's how we ended up \Nattending the WSG Tokyo party.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.01,0:23:34.01,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs19\bord2\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\blur2\c&H222122&\3c&HF1F1F1&\b1\pos(350,109)}WSG Tokyo Sponsor Company Rally
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.37,0:23:38.34,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,However, we had no idea that would be \Nthe start of that horrifying case...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.45,0:23:47.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's a chapel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.10,0:23:51.22,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who invited you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.22,0:23:54.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We received a letter from \Nsomeone named Nichihara Taisei.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.86,0:23:59.70,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone gathered all of us here \Nwhile concealing their identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.90,0:24:05.21,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,This situation is the most \Ncliché of all mystery clichés.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.59,0:24:08.35,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's likely to be serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,The 36-Cell Perfect Game (Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.41,0:24:14.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \N36-Cell Perfect Game, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Snowy Mountain Villa
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.34,0:24:32.30,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.30,0:24:34.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A snowy mountain villa!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:39.91,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.12,0:24:37.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Your nose is red.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.12,0:24:37.70,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Akai?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.70,0:24:39.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1}The Scarlet Bullet{\i0} is available now!
